casebody.data:
The State of Ohio, Appellee, v. El-Amin, Appellant.

[Cite as State v. El-Amin, 130 Ohio St.3d 273, 2011-Ohio-5718.]

(No. 2011-1133 Submitted November 2, 2011 Decided November 9, 2011.) Julia R. Bates, Lucas County Prosecuting Attorney, and Brenda J. Majdalani, Assistant Prosecuting Attorney, for appellee. Deborah Kovac Rump, for appellant.

{¶ 1} The discretionary appeal is accepted.

{¶ 2} The judgment of the court of appeals is vacated, and the cause is remanded to the court of appeals for proceedings consistent with State v. Lester, 130 Ohio St.3d 303, 2011-Ohio-5204, 958 N.E.2d 142.

O’Connoe, C.J., and Pfeifer, Lundberg Stratton, O’Donnell, Cupp, and McGee Brown, JJ., concur. Lanzinger, J., dissents.
